    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what people always say, isn't it? that there's always hope. but it feels so hollow when you've actually lived through it. it's not just a bad phase. it's like... if a glass shatters into a million tiny pieces, you can glue it back together, but it's never a glass again. it's just a pile of sharp edges. maybe some things are just meant to stay broken.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
