      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand that you feel deeply broken, and it's okay to acknowledge that. But even if a glass shatters, pieces can sometimes be put together in a new way, not exactly the same, but still functional and beautiful in its own right. It's okay to feel that some things might never be the same, but it doesn't mean you have to be the same. It's okay to seek help and find a way to piece yourself back together, even if it's not the way you imagined.",
      "source": "target",
