    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but even the \"new way\" of being feels like an exhausting lie. what if the effort of trying to be \"functional\" is actually more painful than just accepting that it's over? it feels like i'm just dragging a corpse around. why do people insist on fighting for something that isn't even there anymore? it just seems so futile.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
